ce:section.ce:para:
A tissue-mimicking phantom was used to illustrate (Fig. 12
                        ) the lesioning caused by HIFU interaction with the egg white protein dispersed in the TMP. The experiments were conducted at a very high energy level of 1.3 J (500 ms, P
                        a = 2.6 W) to obtain a well-defined effect. Furthermore, transducers of different nominal penetration depths in water of 1.3, 1.8 and 2.3 mm were used to illustrate the precision of the energy deposition, as well as a good control of the field distribution at different penetration depths.
